  "type": "mcq",
  "title": "Heat capacity error",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A student conducts an experiment to measure the specific heat capacity, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"c\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"c\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, of a metal. The student heats <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"20.0 grams\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"20.0 grams\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mstyle> <mrow> <mn>20.0</mn> <mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"> </mspace> <mtext>g</mtext> </mrow> </mstyle> </math></span></span> of the metal, adds the heated metal to a calorimeter containing <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"100.0 grams\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"100.0 grams\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>100.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>g</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of water initially at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"18.5 degrees Celsius\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"18.5 degrees Celsius\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>18.5</mn><mi>°</mi><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>, and the mixture comes to thermal equilibrium at <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"19.7 degrees Celsius\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"19.7 degrees Celsius\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>19.7</mn><mi>°</mi><mtext>C</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. Which of the following experimental errors best explains why the value of <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"c\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"c\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>c</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> calculated from the data is smaller than the accepted value for the metal?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The heated metal transfers some thermal energy to the surrounding air before it contacts the water in the calorimeter.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The warmer air in the laboratory transfers thermal energy into the colder water in the calorimeter.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An improperly calibrated balance results in more than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"20.0 grams\"><math alttext=\"20.0 grams\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>20.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>g</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of metal being used in the experiment.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">An improperly calibrated balance results in less than <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"100.0 grams\"><math alttext=\"100.0 grams\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>100.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.25em\"></mspace><mtext>g</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> of water being used in the experiment.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
